{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01EGGfXyMPTFg743yGHF4iAM","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.api;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.json.bind.annotation.JsonbProperty;\n     4→import lombok.*;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.xml.bind.annotation.*;\n     7→\n     8→import java.io.Serializable;\n     9→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ *\n    14→ */\n    15→@Getter\n    16→@Setter\n    17→@ToString\n    18→@EqualsAndHashCode\n    19→@NoArgsConstructor\n    20→@AllArgsConstructor\n    21→@XmlRootElement(name = \"visitList\")\n    22→public class VisitListDto implements Serializable {\n    23→\n    24→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -7588305041391798453L;\n    25→\n    26→    @JsonbProperty(\"visit\")\n    27→    private List<VisitDto> visit = new ArrayList<>();\n    28→\n    29→}\n    30→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"bb55554e-1c40-43dc-83ca-300b606cd531"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01L8S7Ca46o2zPhNkscUw27c","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.api;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     6→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     7→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbException;\n     8→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext;\n     9→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException;\n    10→import jakarta.xml.bind.Marshaller;\n    11→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n    12→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    13→\n    14→import java.io.Serializable;\n    15→import java.io.StringWriter;\n    16→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→\n    19→@Log\n    20→@Stateless\n    21→public class VisitEndpointUtil implements Serializable {\n    22→\n    23→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7444366391126982311L;\n    24→\n    25→    public VisitDto dtoFactory(Visit e) {\n    26→        VisitDto dto = new VisitDto();\n    27→        dto.setId(e.getId());\n    28→        dto.setUuid(e.getUuid());\n    29→        dto.setDate(e.getDate());\n    30→        dto.setDescription(e.getDescription());\n    31→        return dto;\n    32→    }\n    33→\n    34→    public VisitListDto dtoListFactory(List<Visit> eList) {\n    35→        List<VisitDto> dtoList = new ArrayList<>();\n    36→        for (Visit e : eList) {\n    37→            VisitDto dto = this.dtoFactory(e);\n    38→            dtoList.add(dto);\n    39→        }\n    40→        return new VisitListDto(dtoList);\n    41→    }\n    42→\n    43→    public String dtoJsonFactory(VisitDto dto) throws JsonbException {\n    44→        Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    45→        return jsonb.toJson(dto);\n    46→    }\n    47→\n    48→    public String dtoListJsonFactory(VisitListDto listDto) throws JsonbException {\n    49→        Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    50→        return jsonb.toJson(listDto);\n    51→    }\n    52→\n    53→    public String dtoXmlFactory(VisitDto dto) throws JAXBException {\n    54→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(VisitDto.class);\n    55→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    56→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    57→        m.marshal(dto, stringWriter);\n    58→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    public String dtoListXmlFactory(VisitListDto listDto) throws JAXBException {\n    62→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(VisitListDto.class);\n    63→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    64→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    65→        m.marshal(listDto, stringWriter);\n    66→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    67→    }\n    68→}\n    69→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"b7f7973e-81a9-431f-8883-1b8ddeaf8e06"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01VJoheNk2hrG24xoEqFuEgD","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.db.CrudDao;\n     4→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.SearchableEntity;\n     5→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     6→\n     7→/**\n     8→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n     9→ * User: tw\n    10→ * Date: 06.01.14\n    11→ * Time: 09:38\n    12→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    13→ */\n    14→public interface OwnerDao extends CrudDao<Owner>, SearchableEntity<Owner> {\n    15→\n    16→    long serialVersionUID = 4561420558388982124L;\n    17→\n    18→}\n    19→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"d393fe04-8b4b-47ed-8b15-ac4a8f9c2ef0"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01JEqxhgzFo1mY5z2Gg4yabw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n     6→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\n    10→import jakarta.persistence.EntityManager;\n    11→import jakarta.persistence.PersistenceContext;\n    12→import jakarta.persistence.TypedQuery;\n    13→\n    14→import java.io.Serializable;\n    15→import java.util.*;\n    16→\n    17→\n    18→/**\n    19→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n    20→ * User: tw\n    21→ * Date: 06.01.14\n    22→ * Time: 09:38\n    23→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    24→ */\n    25→@Log\n    26→@Stateless\n    27→public class OwnerDaoImpl implements OwnerDao, Serializable {\n    28→\n    29→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 1313423542L;\n    30→\n    31→    @PersistenceContext(unitName = PERSISTENCE_UNIT_NAME)\n    32→    private EntityManager entityManager;\n    33→\n    34→    @Override\n    35→    public List<Owner> getAll() {\n    36→        TypedQuery<Owner> q = entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Owner.getAll\", Owner.class);\n    37→        return q.getResultList();\n    38→    }\n    39→\n    40→    @Override\n    41→    public void delete(long id) {\n    42→        Owner owner = entityManager.find(Owner.class, id);\n    43→        log.info(\"delete Owner: \" + owner.toString());\n    44→        entityManager.remove(owner);\n    45→    }\n    46→\n    47→    @Override\n    48→    public Owner addNew(Owner owner) {\n    49→        owner.setUuid(UUID.randomUUID());\n    50→        //owner.updateSearchindex(); TODO\n    51→        log.info(\"addNew Owner: \" + owner.toString());\n    52→        entityManager.persist(owner);\n    53→        return owner;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    @Override\n    57→    public Owner findById(long id) {\n    58→        return entityManager.find(Owner.class, id);\n    59→    }\n    60→\n    61→    @Override\n    62→    public Owner update(Owner owner) {\n    63→        //owner.updateSearchindex(); TODO\n    64→        log.info(\"update Owner: \" + owner.toString());\n    65→        return entityManager.merge(owner);\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    @Override\n    69→    public List<Owner> search(String searchterm) {\n    70→        log.info(\"search Owner: \" + searchterm);\n    71→        TypedQuery<Owner> q = entityManager.createNamedQuery(\"Owner.search\", Owner.class);\n    72→        q.setParameter(\"searchterm\", \"%\" + searchterm + \"%\");\n    73→        List<Owner> list = q.getResultList();\n    74→        return list;\n    75→    }\n    76→\n    77→    @Override\n    78→    public void resetSearchIndex() {\n    79→\n    80→    }\n    81→\n    82→    @PostConstruct\n    83→    public void postConstruct() {\n    84→        log.info(\"postConstruct: \"+OwnerDaoImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n    85→    }\n    86→\n    87→    @PreDestroy\n    88→    public void preDestroy() {\n    89→        log.info(\"preDestroy: \"+OwnerDaoImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n    90→    }\n    91→}\n    92→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"30cc7360-5575-4654-ba21-82b0106e20f2"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q6cBZJHVa86BgfQvD1pP5w","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     4→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     5→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n     6→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n     7→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.db.CrudService;\n     8→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.application.framework.db.SearchableService;\n     9→\n    10→import java.util.List;\n    11→\n    12→/**\n    13→ * Created by tw on 10.03.14.\n    14→ */\n    15→public interface OwnerService extends CrudService<Owner>, SearchableService<Owner> {\n    16→\n    17→    long serialVersionUID = -5744255576144969978L;\n    18→\n    19→    Visit addNewVisit(@NotNull Visit visit);\n    20→\n    21→    List<Pet> getPetsAsList(@NotNull Owner owner);\n    22→\n    23→    String getPetsAsString(@NotNull Owner owner);\n    24→\n    25→}\n    26→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"ef8e020f-5b76-4f01-9c37-887a3e7c3f60"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_011bgSQtDRDBaCJ5uh8REZc1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     6→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n     7→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.db.PetDao;\n     8→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.db.VisitDao;\n     9→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n    10→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n    11→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    12→\n    13→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n    14→import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\n    15→\n    16→import java.io.Serializable;\n    17→import java.util.List;\n    18→\n    19→/**\n    20→ * Created by tw on 10.03.14.\n    21→ */\n    22→@Log\n    23→@Stateless\n    24→public class OwnerServiceImpl implements OwnerService, Serializable {\n    25→\n    26→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -553095693269912269L;\n    27→\n    28→    @EJB\n    29→    private OwnerDao ownerDao;\n    30→\n    31→    @EJB\n    32→    private PetDao petDao;\n    33→\n    34→    @EJB\n    35→    private VisitDao visitDao;\n    36→\n    37→    @Override\n    38→    public Visit addNewVisit(Visit visit) {\n    39→        log.info(\"addNew Visit: \" + visit.toString());\n    40→        Pet pet = visit.getPet();\n    41→        Owner owner = pet.getOwner();\n    42→        visit.setPet(null);\n    43→        visit = visitDao.addNew(visit);\n    44→        owner = ownerDao.update(owner);\n    45→        pet.setOwner(owner);\n    46→        pet = petDao.update(pet);\n    47→        visit.setPet(pet);\n    48→        visit = visitDao.update(visit);\n    49→        log.info(\"added new Visit - updated owner: \" + owner.toString());\n    50→        log.info(\"added new Visit - updated pet:   \" + pet.toString());\n    51→        log.info(\"added new Visit:                 \" + visit.toString());\n    52→        return visit;\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    @Override\n    56→    public List<Pet> getPetsAsList(@NotNull Owner owner){\n    57→        return petDao.getPetsAsList(owner);\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @Override\n    61→    public String getPetsAsString(@NotNull Owner owner) {\n    62→        StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();\n    63→        for (Pet pet : this.getPetsAsList(owner)) {\n    64→            s.append(pet.getName())\n    65→                    .append(\" (\")\n    66→                    .append(pet.getType().getName())\n    67→                    .append(\") \");\n    68→        }\n    69→        return s.toString();\n    70→    }\n    71→\n    72→    @Override\n    73→    public void resetSearchIndex() {\n    74→        for(Owner owner: this.getAll()){\n    75→            for (Pet pet : this.getPetsAsList(owner)) {\n    76→                for(Visit visit:visitDao.getVisits(pet)){\n    77→                    this.visitDao.update(visit);\n    78→                }\n    79→                this.petDao.update(pet);\n    80→            }\n    81→            this.ownerDao.update(owner);\n    82→        }\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @Override\n    86→    public List<Owner> getAll() {\n    87→        return this.ownerDao.getAll();\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    @Override\n    91→    public void delete(long id) {\n    92→        this.ownerDao.delete(id);\n    93→    }\n    94→\n    95→    @Override\n    96→    public Owner addNew(Owner owner) {\n    97→        //owner = this.updateSearchindex(owner); TODO\n    98→        log.info(\"addNew Owner: \" + owner.toString());\n    99→        return this.ownerDao.addNew(owner);\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    @Override\n   103→    public Owner findById(long id) {\n   104→        return this.ownerDao.findById(id);\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    @Override\n   108→    public Owner update(Owner owner) {\n   109→        //owner = this.updateSearchindex(owner); TODO\n   110→        log.info(\"update Owner: \" + owner.toString());\n   111→        return this.ownerDao.update(owner);\n   112→    }\n   113→\n   114→    private Owner updateSearchindex(Owner owner) {\n   115→        //TODO\n   116→        for(Pet pet:this.petDao.getPetsAsList(owner)){\n   117→            for(Visit visit:visitDao.getVisits(pet)){\n   118→                this.visitDao.update(visit);\n   119→            }\n   120→            this.petDao.update(pet);\n   121→        }\n   122→        return owner;\n   123→    }\n   124→\n   125→    @Override\n   126→    public List<Owner> search(String searchterm) {\n   127→        return this.ownerDao.search(searchterm);\n   128→    }\n   129→\n   130→    @PostConstruct\n   131→    public void postConstruct() {\n   132→        log.info(\"postConstruct: \"+OwnerServiceImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    @PreDestroy\n   136→    public void preDestroy() {\n   137→        log.info(\"preDestroy: \"+OwnerServiceImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n   138→    }\n   139→}\n   140→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"416dc391-f047-4bbe-a255-69eac6d35c4b"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_0183GR3RyVYFiRmCrkayvpJY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     4→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n     5→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.PetType;\n     6→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n     7→\n     8→import java.io.Serializable;\n     9→import java.util.List;\n    10→\n    11→public interface OwnerViewService extends Serializable {\n    12→\n    13→    List<Pet> getPetsAsList(Owner owner);\n    14→\n    15→    String getPetsAsString(Owner owner);\n    16→\n    17→    List<Visit> getVisits(Pet ownersPet);\n    18→\n    19→    Visit addNewVisit(Visit visit);\n    20→\n    21→    Pet addNewPet(Pet pet);\n    22→\n    23→    Pet findPetById(long id);\n    24→\n    25→    Pet updatePet(Pet pet);\n    26→\n    27→    Owner findOwnerById(long id);\n    28→\n    29→    Owner updateOwner(Owner entity);\n    30→\n    31→    Owner addNewOwner(Owner entity);\n    32→\n    33→    void deleteOwner(long ownerId);\n    34→\n    35→    List<Owner> getAllOwner();\n    36→\n    37→    List<Owner> searchOwner(String searchterm);\n    38→\n    39→    PetType findPetTypeById(long petTypeId);\n    40→\n    41→    List<PetType> getAllPetType();\n    42→\n    43→}\n    44→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"4d06c44f-3bca-4299-9b96-2bf8dae559dc"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Cg5ZeAEtbXSCqnfCqHo2GC","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.db;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     4→import jakarta.annotation.PreDestroy;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     6→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     7→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n     8→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner.Owner;\n     9→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n    10→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.db.PetDao;\n    11→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.PetType;\n    12→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.db.PetTypeDao;\n    13→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.db.PetTypeService;\n    14→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    15→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.db.VisitDao;\n    16→\n    17→import java.io.Serializable;\n    18→import java.util.List;\n    19→\n    20→@Log\n    21→@Stateless\n    22→public class OwnerViewServiceImpl implements OwnerViewService, Serializable {\n    23→\n    24→    private static final long serialVersionUID = -553095668269912269L;\n    25→\n    26→    @EJB\n    27→    private PetTypeDao petTypeDao;\n    28→\n    29→    @EJB\n    30→    private OwnerDao ownerDao;\n    31→\n    32→    @EJB\n    33→    private VisitDao visitDao;\n    34→\n    35→    @EJB\n    36→    private PetDao petDao;\n    37→\n    38→    @Override\n    39→    public void deleteOwner(long ownerId) {\n    40→        Owner owner = ownerDao.findById(ownerId);\n    41→        for(Pet pet:petDao.getPetsAsList(owner)){\n    42→            for(Visit visit:visitDao.getVisits(pet)){\n    43→                visitDao.delete(visit.getId());\n    44→            }\n    45→            petDao.delete(pet.getId());\n    46→        }\n    47→        ownerDao.delete(ownerId);\n    48→    }\n    49→\n    50→    @Override\n    51→    public List<Owner> getAllOwner() {\n    52→        return ownerDao.getAll();\n    53→    }\n    54→\n    55→    @Override\n    56→    public Owner findOwnerById(long id) {\n    57→        return ownerDao.findById(id);\n    58→    }\n    59→\n    60→    @Override\n    61→    public Owner updateOwner(Owner entity) {\n    62→        return ownerDao.update(entity);\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    @Override\n    66→    public Owner addNewOwner(Owner entity) {\n    67→        return ownerDao.addNew(entity);\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    @Override\n    71→    public List<Owner> searchOwner(String searchterm) {\n    72→        return ownerDao.search(searchterm);\n    73→    }\n    74→\n    75→    @Override\n    76→    public PetType findPetTypeById(long petTypeId) {\n    77→        return petTypeDao.findById(petTypeId);\n    78→    }\n    79→\n    80→    @Override\n    81→    public List<PetType> getAllPetType() {\n    82→        return petTypeDao.getAll();\n    83→    }\n    84→\n    85→    @Override\n    86→    public List<Pet> getPetsAsList(Owner owner) {\n    87→        return petDao.getPetsAsList(owner);\n    88→    }\n    89→\n    90→    @Override\n    91→    public String getPetsAsString(Owner owner) {\n    92→        StringBuilder s = new StringBuilder();\n    93→        for (Pet pet : this.getPetsAsList(owner)) {\n    94→            s.append(pet.getName())\n    95→                    .append(\" (\")\n    96→                    .append(pet.getType().getName())\n    97→                    .append(\") \");\n    98→        }\n    99→        return s.toString();\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    @Override\n   103→    public Pet addNewPet(Pet pet) {\n   104→        return petDao.addNew(pet);\n   105→    }\n   106→\n   107→    @Override\n   108→    public Pet findPetById(long id) {\n   109→        return petDao.findById(id);\n   110→    }\n   111→\n   112→    @Override\n   113→    public Pet updatePet(Pet pet) {\n   114→        return petDao.update(pet);\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    @Override\n   118→    public List<Visit> getVisits(Pet ownersPet) {\n   119→        return visitDao.getVisits(ownersPet);\n   120→    }\n   121→\n   122→    @Override\n   123→    public Visit addNewVisit(Visit visit) {\n   124→        return visitDao.addNew(visit);\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→\n   128→    @PostConstruct\n   129→    public void postConstruct() {\n   130→        log.info(\"postConstruct: \"+OwnerViewServiceImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n   131→    }\n   132→\n   133→    @PreDestroy\n   134→    public void preDestroy() {\n   135→        log.info(\"preDestroy: \"+OwnerViewServiceImpl.class.getSimpleName());\n   136→    }\n   137→}\n   138→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_018DtVevZJV7iQdpgxiKdQTP","session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"4afe7c52-ad9f-4827-ad59-20567a9b27d9"}
