{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01MaHCAiw8vszYwfF86jTYe8","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.api;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.ejb.EJB;\n     5→import jakarta.ejb.Stateless;\n     6→import jakarta.json.bind.Jsonb;\n     7→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbBuilder;\n     8→import jakarta.json.bind.JsonbException;\n     9→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBContext;\n    10→import jakarta.xml.bind.JAXBException;\n    11→import jakarta.xml.bind.Marshaller;\n    12→import lombok.extern.java.Log;\n    13→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.Pet;\n    14→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pet.db.PetService;\n    15→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.api.PetTypeDto;\n    16→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.pettype.api.PetTypeEndpointUtil;\n    17→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.Visit;\n    18→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.api.VisitEndpointUtil;\n    19→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.visit.api.VisitListDto;\n    20→\n    21→import java.io.Serializable;\n    22→import java.io.StringWriter;\n    23→import java.util.ArrayList;\n    24→import java.util.List;\n    25→\n    26→\n    27→@Log\n    28→@Stateless\n    29→public class PetEndpointUtil implements Serializable {\n    30→\n    31→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7444366391126982311L;\n    32→\n    33→    @EJB\n    34→    private PetTypeEndpointUtil petTypeEndpointUtil;\n    35→\n    36→    @EJB\n    37→    private VisitEndpointUtil visitEndpointUtil;\n    38→\n    39→    @EJB\n    40→    private PetService petService;\n    41→\n    42→    public PetDto dtoFactory(Pet pet) {\n    43→        PetDto dto = new PetDto();\n    44→        dto.setId(pet.getId());\n    45→        dto.setUuid(pet.getUuid());\n    46→        dto.setBirthDate(pet.getBirthDate());\n    47→        dto.setName(pet.getName());\n    48→        PetTypeDto oPetTypeDto =this.petTypeEndpointUtil.dtoFactory(pet.getType());\n    49→        dto.setPetType(oPetTypeDto);\n    50→        List<Visit> visitList = petService.getVisits(pet);\n    51→        VisitListDto oVisitListDto =this.visitEndpointUtil.dtoListFactory(visitList);\n    52→        dto.setVisitList(oVisitListDto);\n    53→        return dto;\n    54→    }\n    55→\n    56→    public PetListDto dtoListFactory(List<Pet> petList) {\n    57→        List<PetDto> dtoList = new ArrayList<>();\n    58→        for (Pet pet : petList) {\n    59→            PetDto dto = this.dtoFactory(pet);\n    60→            dtoList.add(dto);\n    61→        }\n    62→        return new PetListDto(dtoList);\n    63→    }\n    64→\n    65→    public String dtoListJsonFactory(PetListDto listDto) throws JsonbException {\n    66→        Jsonb jsonb = JsonbBuilder.create();\n    67→        return jsonb.toJson(listDto);\n    68→    }\n    69→\n    70→    public String dtoXmlFactory(PetDto dto) throws JAXBException {\n    71→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(PetDto.class);\n    72→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    73→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    74→        m.marshal(dto, stringWriter);\n    75→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    76→    }\n    77→\n    78→    public String dtoListXmlFactory(PetListDto listDto) throws JAXBException {\n    79→        JAXBContext jc = JAXBContext.newInstance(PetListDto.class);\n    80→        Marshaller m = jc.createMarshaller();\n    81→        StringWriter stringWriter = new StringWriter();\n    82→        m.marshal(listDto, stringWriter);\n    83→        return stringWriter.toString();\n    84→    }\n    85→}\n    86→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about th