tclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/specialty/db/SpecialtyServiceImpl.java`\n8. **SpecialtyService.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/specialty/db/SpecialtyService.java`\n9. **VetServiceImpl.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/vet/db/VetServiceImpl.java`\n10. **VetService.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/vet/db/VetService.java`\n11. **VisitServiceImpl.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/visit/db/VisitServiceImpl.java`\n12. **VisitService.java** - `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__petclinic__jakarta__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/org/woehlke/jakartaee/petclinic/visit/db/VisitService.java`\n\n### Key Changes Applied:\n\n**For Service Implementation Classes:**\n- Replaced `@Stateless` with `@Service` and `@Transactional`\n- Replaced `@EJB` with `@Autowired` for dependency injection\n- Replaced DAO interfaces with Spring Data Repository interfaces (e.g., `OwnerDao` → `OwnerRepository`)\n- Replaced DAO method calls with Repository methods (e.g., `dao.addNew()` → `repository.save()`, `dao.getAll()` → `repository.findAllOrderByName()`, `dao.delete()` → `repository.deleteById()`)\n- Removed `Serializable` interface (not needed in Spring)\n- Kept `@PostConstruct` and `@PreDestroy` annotations (these work with Spring and use jakarta.annotation package)\n- Added UUID generation for new entities in service layer\n- Simplified `resetSearchIndex()` methods to no-op implementations\n- Used constructor-based dependency injection with `@Autowired`\n- Changed methods to use `Optional` properly (e.g., `repository.findById(id).orElse(null)`)\n\n**For Service Interface Classes:**\n- No structural changes needed - interfaces remain clean\n- Removed Jakarta EE-specific imports\n- Kept `Serializable` where it was already present in the original interfaces\n\nAll services now use Spring Boot's dependency injection, transaction management, and Spring Data JPA repositories instead of Jakarta EE's EJB and DAO patterns."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"a34a00f5-e561-4ea9-8355-76b86fb60460"}
