{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01R5cVSGuzNJuBsNdQyHpy38","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.owner;\n     2→\n     3→import jakarta.validation.constraints.*;\n     4→import lombok.*;\n     5→\n     6→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n     7→\n     8→import java.io.Serializable;\n     9→import java.util.*;\n    10→\n    11→/**\n    12→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n    13→ * User: tw\n    14→ * Date: 01.01.14\n    15→ * Time: 21:08\n    16→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    17→ */\n    18→@Entity\n    19→@Getter\n    20→@Setter\n    21→@ToString\n    22→@NoArgsConstructor\n    23→@AllArgsConstructor\n    24→@Table(\n    25→        name = Owner.TABLENAME,\n    26→        uniqueConstraints = {\n    27→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    28→                        name = Owner.TABLENAME + \"_unique_uuid\",\n    29→                        columnNames = {Owner.COL_UUID}\n    30→                ),\n    31→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    32→                        name = Owner.TABLENAME + \"_unique_email\",\n    33→                        columnNames = {Owner.COL_EMAIL}\n    34→                ),\n    35→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    36→                        name = Owner.TABLENAME + \"_unique_names\",\n    37→                        columnNames = {\n    38→                                Owner.COL_FIRSTNAME,\n    39→                                Owner.COL_LASTNAME,\n    40→                                Owner.COL_CITY,\n    41→                                Owner.COL_PHONENUMBER\n    42→                        }\n    43→                )\n    44→        }\n    45→)\n    46→@NamedQueries({\n    47→        @NamedQuery(\n    48→                name = \"Owner.getAll\",\n    49→                query = \"select o from Owner o order by o.lastName,o.firstName asc\"\n    50→        ),\n    51→        @NamedQuery(\n    52→                name = \"Owner.search\",\n    53→                query = \"select o from Owner o where o.searchindex like :searchterm order by o.lastName,o.firstName asc\"\n    54→        )\n    55→})\n    56→public class Owner implements Comparable<Owner>, Serializable {\n    57→\n    58→    public final static String TABLENAME = \"owner\";\n    59→    public final static String COL_ID = \"id\";\n    60→    public final static String COL_UUID = \"uuid\";\n    61→    public final static String COL_FIRSTNAME = \"first_name\";\n    62→    public final static String COL_LASTNAME = \"lastName\";\n    63→    public final static String COL_ADDRESS = \"address\";\n    64→    public final static String COL_HOUSENUMBER = \"housenumber\";\n    65→    public final static String COL_ADDRESS_INFO = \"address_info\";\n    66→    public final static String COL_CITY = \"city\";\n    67→    public final static String COL_ZIPCODE = \"zipcode\";\n    68→    public final static String COL_PHONENUMBER = \"phonenumber\";\n    69→    public final static String COL_EMAIL = \"email\";\n    70→    public final static String COL_SEARCHINDEX = \"searchindex\";\n    71→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 7995827646591579744L;\n    72→\n    73→    @Id\n    74→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = \"owner_gen\")\n    75→    @SequenceGenerator(name=\"owner_gen\", sequenceName=\"owner_seq\")\n    76→    private Long id;\n    77→\n    78→    @Column(name = COL_UUID, nullable = false, unique = true, length = 36)\n    79→    private UUID uuid;\n    80→\n    81→    @Column(name = COL_SEARCHINDEX)\n    82→    private String searchindex;\n    83→\n    84→    @Column(name = COL_FIRSTNAME, nullable = false)\n    85→    @NotEmpty\n    86→    private String firstName;\n    87→\n    88→    @Column(name = COL_LASTNAME, nullable = false)\n    89→    @NotEmpty\n    90→    private String lastName;\n    91→\n    92→    @Column(name = COL_ADDRESS, nullable = false)\n    93→    @NotEmpty\n    94→    private String address;\n    95→\n    96→    @Column(name = COL_HOUSENUMBER, nullable = false)\n    97→    @NotEmpty\n    98→    private String houseNumber;\n    99→\n   100→    @Column(name = COL_ADDRESS_INFO)\n   101→    private String addressInfo;\n   102→\n   103→    @Column(name = COL_CITY, nullable = false)\n   104→    @NotEmpty\n   105→    private String city;\n   106→\n   107→    @Column(name = COL_ZIPCODE, nullable = false)\n   108→    @NotEmpty\n   109→    //@Digits(fraction = 0, integer = 5)\n   110→    @Pattern(regexp = \"\\\\w{1,7}\\\\s{0,1}\\\\w{1,7}\\\\s{0,1}\\\\w{1,7}\", message = \"{invalid.zipCode}\")\n   111→    private String zipCode;\n   112→\n   113→    @Column(name = COL_PHONENUMBER, nullable = false)\n   114→    @NotEmpty\n   115→    @Pattern(regexp = \"\\\\+[1-9][0-9]\\\\s{0,1}[0-9]{0,5}\\\\s{0,1}[0-9]{4,16}\",\n   116→            message = \"{invalid.phoneNumber}\")\n   117→    private String phoneNumber;\n   118→\n   119→    @Column(name = COL_EMAIL, nullable = false, unique = true)\n   120→    @NotEmpty\n   121→    @Email\n   122→    private String email;\n   123→\n   124→    @Transient\n   125→    public String getFullname(){\n   126→        return this.lastName +\", \"+this.firstName;\n   127→    }\n   128→\n   129→    @Transient\n   130→    public String getTableName() {\n   131→        return TABLENAME;\n   132→    }\n   133→\n   134→    @Transient\n   135→    public String getPrimaryKey() {\n   136→        return \"\" + this.getFullName() + \" ( \" + this.getCity() + \" ) \";\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    public void setPrimaryKey(String primaryKey) {\n   140→    }\n   141→\n   142→    @Transient\n   143→    public String getPrimaryKeyWithId() {\n   144→        return this.getPrimaryKey() + \"(\" + this.getId() + \",\" + this.getUuid() + \")\";\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    public void updateSearchindex() {\n   148→        List<String> l = new ArrayList<>();\n   149→        l.add(this.getFirstName());\n   150→        l.add(this.getLastName());\n   151→        l.add(this.getAddress());\n   152→        if(null != this.getAddressInfo()){\n   153→            l.add(this.getAddressInfo());\n   154→        }\n   155→        l.add(this.getHouseNumber());\n   156→        l.add(this.getZipCode());\n   157→        l.add(this.getCity());\n   158→        l.add(this.getPhoneNumber());\n   159→        l.add(this.getEmail());\n   160→        StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\n   161→        for(String ll:l){\n   162→            for(String e:ll.split(\"\\\\W\")){\n   163→                b.append(e);\n   164→                b.append(\" \");\n   165→            }\n   166→        }\n   167→        this.setSearchindex(b.toString());\n   168→    }\n   169→\n   170→    @Transient\n   171→    public String getFullName() {\n   172→        return this.lastName + \", \" + this.firstName;\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    @Override\n   176→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   177→        if (this == o) return true;\n   178→        if (!(o instanceof Owner)) return false;\n   179→        Owner owner = (Owner) o;\n   180→        return getFirstName().equals(owner.getFirstName()) && getLastName().equals(owner.getLastName()) && Objects.equals(getAddress(), owner.getAddress()) && Objects.equals(getHouseNumber(), owner.getHouseNumber()) && Objects.equals(getAddressInfo(), owner.getAddressInfo()) && Objects.equals(getCity(), owner.getCity()) && Objects.equals(getZipCode(), owner.getZipCode()) && getPhoneNumber().equals(owner.getPhoneNumber()) && getEmail().equals(owner.getEmail());\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Override\n   184→    public int hashCode() {\n   185→        return Objects.hash(getFirstName(), getLastName(), getAddress(), getHouseNumber(), getAddressInfo(), getCity(), getZipCode(), getPhoneNumber(), getEmail());\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    @Override\n   189→    public int compareTo(Owner o) {\n   190→        return this.getFullname().compareTo(o.getFullname());\n   191→    }\n   192→}\n   193→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"99dff665-d784-4a4b-9db2-ff3ca3208613"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01T1R7BfoF2oaTePmfGp7aZh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.vet;\n     2→\n     3→\n     4→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotBlank;\n     5→import jakarta.validation.constraints.NotNull;\n     6→import lombok.*;\n     7→import org.woehlke.jakartaee.petclinic.specialty.Specialty;\n     8→\n     9→import jakarta.persistence.*;\n    10→\n    11→import java.io.Serializable;\n    12→import java.util.*;\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * Created with IntelliJ IDEA.\n    16→ * User: tw\n    17→ * Date: 01.01.14\n    18→ * Time: 21:10\n    19→ * To change this template use File | Settings | File Templates.\n    20→ */\n    21→@Entity\n    22→@Getter\n    23→@Setter\n    24→@ToString\n    25→@NoArgsConstructor\n    26→@AllArgsConstructor\n    27→@Table(\n    28→        name = Vet.TABLENAME,\n    29→        uniqueConstraints = {\n    30→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    31→                        name = Vet.TABLENAME + \"_unique_uuid\",\n    32→                        columnNames = {Vet.COL_UUID}\n    33→                ),\n    34→                @UniqueConstraint(\n    35→                        name = Vet.TABLENAME + \"_unique_names\",\n    36→                        columnNames = {Vet.COL_FIRSTNAME,Vet.COL_LASTNAME}\n    37→                )\n    38→        }\n    39→)\n    40→@NamedQueries({\n    41→        @NamedQuery(\n    42→                name = \"Vet.getAll\",\n    43→                query = \"select s from Vet s order by s.lastName, s.firstName\"\n    44→        ),\n    45→        @NamedQuery(\n    46→                name = \"Vet.search\",\n    47→                query = \"select v from Vet v where v.searchindex like :searchterm\"\n    48→        )\n    49→})\n    50→public class Vet implements Comparable<Vet>, Serializable {\n    51→\n    52→    private static final long serialVersionUID = 6749793465861123385L;\n    53→\n    54→    public final static String XML_ROOT_ELEMENT_NAME = \"vet\";\n    55→    public final static String TABLENAME = \"vet\";\n    56→    public final static String COL_ID = \"id\";\n    57→    public final static String COL_UUID = \"uuid\";\n    58→    public final static String COL_FIRSTNAME = \"first_name\";\n    59→    public final static String COL_LASTNAME = \"lastName\";\n    60→    public final static String COL_VET_SPECIALTIES = \"vet_specialties\";\n    61→    public final static String COL_JOIN_VET_ID = \"vet_id\";\n    62→    public final static String COL_JOIN_SPECIALTY_ID = \"specialty_id\";\n    63→    public final static String COL_SEARCHINDEX = \"searchindex\";\n    64→\n    65→    @Id\n    66→    @GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.SEQUENCE, generator = \"vet_gen\")\n    67→    @SequenceGenerator(name=\"vet_gen\", sequenceName=\"vet_seq\")\n    68→    private Long id;\n    69→\n    70→    @Column(name = COL_UUID, nullable = false, unique = true, length = 36)\n    71→    private UUID uuid;\n    72→\n    73→    @Column(name = COL_SEARCHINDEX, nullable = true)\n    74→    private String searchindex;\n    75→\n    76→    @NotBlank\n    77→    @Column(name = COL_FIRSTNAME, nullable = false)\n    78→    private String firstName;\n    79→\n    80→    @NotBlank\n    81→    @Column(name = COL_LASTNAME, nullable = false)\n    82→    private String lastName;\n    83→\n    84→    @NotNull\n    85→    @ManyToMany(fetch = FetchType.EAGER)\n    86→    @JoinTable(name = COL_VET_SPECIALTIES,\n    87→            joinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = COL_JOIN_VET_ID),\n    88→            inverseJoinColumns = @JoinColumn(name = COL_JOIN_SPECIALTY_ID))\n    89→    private Set<Specialty> specialties = new HashSet<>();\n    90→\n    91→    public Vet(@NotBlank String firstName, @NotBlank String lastName) {\n    92→        this.specialties = new HashSet<>();\n    93→        this.firstName = firstName;\n    94→        this.lastName = lastName;\n    95→    }\n    96→\n    97→    @Transient\n    98→    public String getFullname(){\n    99→        return this.lastName +\", \"+this.firstName;\n   100→    }\n   101→\n   102→    @Transient\n   103→    public String getSpecialtiesAsString() {\n   104→        StringBuilder stringBuilder = new StringBuilder();\n   105→        if (getNrOfSpecialties() == 0) {\n   106→            stringBuilder.append(\"none\");\n   107→        } else {\n   108→            for (Specialty specialty : getSpecialties()) {\n   109→                stringBuilder.append(specialty.getName());\n   110→                stringBuilder.append(\" \");\n   111→            }\n   112→        }\n   113→        return stringBuilder.toString();\n   114→    }\n   115→\n   116→    @Transient\n   117→    public List<Specialty> getSpecialtiesAsList() {\n   118→        List<Specialty> listSpecialty = new ArrayList<>();\n   119→        Set<Specialty> setSpecialty = this.getSpecialties();\n   120→        for(Specialty specialty: setSpecialty){\n   121→            listSpecialty.add(specialty);\n   122→        }\n   123→        Collections.sort(listSpecialty);\n   124→        return listSpecialty;\n   125→    }\n   126→\n   127→    public int getNrOfSpecialties() {\n   128→        return this.specialties.size();\n   129→    }\n   130→\n   131→    public void addSpecialty(Specialty specialty) {\n   132→        this.specialties.add(specialty);\n   133→    }\n   134→\n   135→    public void removeSpecialties() {\n   136→        this.specialties.clear();\n   137→    }\n   138→\n   139→    @Transient\n   140→    public String getTableName() {\n   141→        return TABLENAME;\n   142→    }\n   143→\n   144→    @Transient\n   145→    public String getPrimaryKey() {\n   146→        return lastName + \" \" + firstName;\n   147→    }\n   148→\n   149→    @Transient\n   150→    public String getPrimaryKeyWithId() {\n   151→        return this.getPrimaryKey() + \"(\" + this.getId() + \",\" + this.getUuid() + \")\";\n   152→    }\n   153→\n   154→    public void updateSearchindex() {\n   155→        List<String> vetElements = new ArrayList<>();\n   156→        for(String element :this.getFirstName().split(\"\\\\W\")){\n   157→            vetElements.add(element);\n   158→        }\n   159→        for(String element :this.getLastName().split(\"\\\\W\")){\n   160→            vetElements.add(element);\n   161→        }\n   162→        for(Specialty s: this.getSpecialties()){\n   163→            for(String element :s.getName().split(\"\\\\W\")) {\n   164→                vetElements.add(element);\n   165→            }\n   166→        }\n   167→        StringBuilder b = new StringBuilder();\n   168→        for(String e: vetElements){\n   169→            b.append(e);\n   170→            b.append(\" \");\n   171→        }\n   172→        this.setSearchindex(b.toString());\n   173→    }\n   174→\n   175→    @Override\n   176→    public boolean equals(Object o) {\n   177→        if (this == o) return true;\n   178→        if (!(o instanceof Vet)) return false;\n   179→        Vet vet = (Vet) o;\n   180→        return getFirstName().equals(vet.getFirstName()) && getLastName().equals(vet.getLastName()) && getSpecialties().equals(vet.getSpecialties());\n   181→    }\n   182→\n   183→    @Override\n   184→    public int hashCode() {\n   185→        return Objects.hash(getFirstName(), getLastName(), getSpecialties());\n   186→    }\n   187→\n   188→    @Override\n   189→    public int compareTo(Vet o) {\n   190→        return this.getFullname().compareTo(o.getFullname());\n   191→    }\n   192→}\n   193→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"f7ea4ab9-a75a-42cd-bd7b-9adf1fccce54"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_bdrk_01N8kXh3AauPuJ2c9wHu9sKf","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I see the full picture. The entity has:\n- `COL_LASTNAME = \"lastName\"` (camelCase) \n- `COL_FIRSTNAME = \"first_name\"` (snake_case already)\n\nWith Spring Boot's default `SpringPhysicalNamingStrategy`, the `@Column(name = \"lastName\")` gets transformed to `last_name`. The cleanest fix is to use `PhysicalNamingStrategyStandardImpl` so that `@Column` names are used verbatim, and then update `data.sql` to use the exact `@Column` names. But since `COL_LASTNAME = \"lastName\"` is camelCase, PostgreSQL will lowercase it to `lastname` unless quoted.\n\nActually, the best approach is to just normalize the entity constants to all be snake_case, matching what Spring's naming strategy produces. Let me fix the `COL_LASTNAME` constant in both Owner and Vet entities from `\"lastName\"` to `\"last_name\"`, and then update `data.sql` accordingly.\n\nWait - let me think about this more carefully. With `SpringPhysicalNamingStrategy`:\n- `@Column(name = \"lastName\")` → `last_name`\n- `@Column(name = \"first_name\")` → `first_name` \n- `@Column(name = \"housenumber\")` → `housenumber`\n- `@Column(name = \"zipcode\")` → `zipcode`\n\nSo the data.sql should use: `last_name`, `first_name`, `housenumber`, `zipcode`, `phonenumber`, `searchindex`, `address_info`.\n\nThe current data.sql uses `lastname` (not `last_name`). Let me fix data.sql to match the actual Hibernate-generated column names:"}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5929,"cache_read_input_tokens":34960,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5929,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1240},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f3e9f2b3-1305-43ae-9feb-99d287ff0491","uuid":"9e96edbc-c42f-4e56-8d04-706afb5cd665"}
